        "title": "fix(msteams): truncate reflection prompt on a UTF-16 boundary",
        "body": "## Problem\nThe feedback reflection prompt truncation slices on UTF-16 code units, so an emoji at the boundary is cut into a lone surrogate that then goes into the LLM prompt text.\n\n## Fix\nUse the shared `truncateUtf16Safe` helper so truncation stops on a whole code-point boundary.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in `extensions/msteams/src/feedback-reflection.test.ts` — fails before, passes after. Pure unit test.\n",
